# CODEOWNERS — the hard human-review backstop for the unattended auto-merge pipeline.
#
# With "Require review from Code Owners" enabled in the branch ruleset (see
# docs/auto-merge.md), any PR that touches a code-owned path below needs an actual
# code owner's approval before it can merge. The fleet/automation bot is NOT a code
# owner, so it physically cannot self-approve these — the dangerous ~5% of paths stop
# for a human while everything else flows through the checks-only green path.
#
# Last match wins (GitHub CODEOWNERS semantics). Keep these globs in lockstep with any
# risky-path pre-filter in the auto-merge automation; CODEOWNERS is the authoritative stop.

# Default: no owner -> agent path, gated only by the `verify` checks (this is intended).

# CI/CD, the gates themselves, secret usage, this very file.
/.github/                @Eyalm321

# GPU/GUI surface — heavy, hardware-dependent, not exercised by the per-PR test gate.
/rs/crates/app/          @Eyalm321

# build.rs = arbitrary code execution at build time.
**/build.rs              @Eyalm321

# Dependency / supply-chain changes.
**/Cargo.toml            @Eyalm321
**/Cargo.lock            @Eyalm321
